race.comment: NORTH COURT (3) resumes and scored back-to-back wins before running below his best last time. The lightly raced galloper will be naturally improved and a bold run is anticipated. PUREZZA (4) led and just missed this grade last time spiking his figures. She will jump and run from the inside barrier and just has to hold the form to threaten. THE LOUVRE (1) put two on end before a plainer effort last time. Better suited today with a 3kg claim atop and maps to get every chance. GIDDAY GIDDAY (2) is a second-up winner who can make quick improvement. The 2kg claim assists but the gate requires a good ride. RED COBRA (5) resumed and has switched from a NSW yard. He has won fresh and a betting watch is advised.
